						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Achyutadēva Mahārāya Year: Śaka 145[1], <hi rend="italic">Virōdhi, Paṅguṉi, 18.</hi></hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a gift of eighty <hi rend="italic">(paṇam ?)</hi> by Mallappanāyakkar, an official <hi rend="italic">(aḍaippattu)</hi> of the ruler Achchutayadēva Mahārāya for conducting offerings and worship to the god, Tirumalar-uḍaiyanayiṉār at Dēvukāpuram.</p>						

						<p>The temple accountant Uttaṇḍi figures as signatory.</p>						

						</summary>
